# Agent Workflow & Documentation Protocol

# Development Flow (per wave)
1. Discuss task; record decisions in `docs/DECISIONS.md`.
2. Write plan to `docs/plans/NN-name.md` (checkboxes per file/task).
3. Set `Active plan` in `docs/PROGRESS.md` only (no checkbox copy yet).
4. Implement; mark `[x]` in the **active plan** as work completes.
5. Test (unit; smoke/integration when affected).
6. Commit (see `06-git-workflow.mdc`).
7. Archive the wave in `docs/PROGRESS.md` (append journal; clear or update `Active plan`).

# Session Types
- Ask/Plan: High-level discussion and decomposition.
  End with "запиши решения и сохрани план".
  No code generation.
- Agent: One plan item per chat. Code only.

# Session Start (Mandatory)
- Read @docs/INDEX.md — project navigation map.
- Read @docs/PROGRESS.md — find `Active plan` pointer.
- Read the active plan file from `docs/plans/`.
- Proceed only after understanding current state and scope.

# Session End (Mandatory)
After any code change, always update docs/:
- **Active plan file:** mark completed items `[x]`; change scope or add checkboxes only if scope changed (routine progress stays in the plan, not in PROGRESS).
- DECISIONS.md: append any architectural decision made during this session.
- INDEX.md: update if a file was created, deleted, or changed its purpose.
- **ARCHITECTURE.md:** update when the change affects runtime architecture: module boundaries (`src/core|operations|adapters|mcp_servers`), major flows (discover → choose → walk → build), tool transport/execution (MCP / `<tool_call>`), or artifacts/logs layout.
- **PROGRESS.md:** only when the wave is closed (step 7) — see "Archive wave" below.

# Plans
- Each development phase has its own file: `docs/plans/NN-name.md` (e.g. `02-mcp-http-smoke-script.md`).
- Plans are immutable once started. Do not rewrite completed history in plan files.
- **Working checklist:** checkboxes `[ ]` / `[x]` / `[-]` are maintained in the active plan during implementation.
- Use checkboxes: `[ ]` pending, `[x]` done, `[-]` skipped with reason.

# On-Demand Documentation Commands

When user says "запиши решения" or "сохрани решения":
- Extract all architectural decisions from current chat history.
- Append to `docs/DECISIONS.md` in the specified format.
- Use today's date in `[YYYY-MM-DD]` format for each entry.
- Show the user what was written for review.

When user says "запиши план" or "сохрани план":
- Generate a structured plan based on current chat.
- Save to `docs/plans/NN-name.md` with checkboxes per file/function.
- Update `docs/PROGRESS.md`: set `Active plan: docs/plans/NN-name.md` only (optional 1–2 line goal summary; **do not** copy plan checkboxes).
- Ask user to confirm the plan number and name before saving.

# Archive wave (PROGRESS.md, after commit)
When a plan wave is finished and committed:
- Append a new section to the **end** of the journal in `docs/PROGRESS.md`.
- Section header: plan path and short title (e.g. `## Wave: docs/plans/03-operations-layer.md`).
- Copy all plan checkboxes with their **final** state (`[x]` / `[-]`).
- Set `Active plan: none` or point to the next plan if already started.
- Do not insert archived sections above older waves.

# PROGRESS.md Roles
- **Top:** `Active plan: docs/plans/NN-name.md` or `Active plan: none` — status pointer only.
- **Body (journal):** archived completed waves; full checkbox lists copied from plans at archive time.
- **Not** a live duplicate of the active plan during implementation.

# PROGRESS.md Format (journal section)
## Wave: docs/plans/NN-name.md — short title

- [x] Completed task — `src/path/file.py`
- [-] Skipped task — reason

# PROGRESS.md Journal Order (Mandatory)
- Journal sections are chronological: oldest wave at the top of the journal, newest **appended to the end**.
- `Active plan` stays at the very top and is not part of journal ordering.
- If ordering is broken, fix it in the same session as part of documentation sync.

# INDEX.md Format
- One line per file: `path/to/file.py` — what it contains and why it exists.
- Grouped by directory.
- Updated when files are created, deleted, or change purpose (session end or archive).

# DECISIONS.md Format
- New decision blocks are **appended to the end** of the file (chronological journal, top-to-bottom read order). Do not insert new entries above older ones.
## [YYYY-MM-DD] Short title
**Decision:** What was decided.
**Reason:** Why.
**Rejected:** What was considered and dropped (if any).

# Periodic Lint (every few sessions)
Open an Ask chat with @docs/INDEX.md @docs/PROGRESS.md @docs/DECISIONS.md and the active plan.
Ask: "Are there contradictions between decisions and the current plan? What is outdated?"
